Secure Architecture and Threat Modelling

Understanding of threat modelling 
      - purpose of threat modelling
            - use cases for which threat modelling is used 
                identifying threats for a solution so mitigations can be documented
                etc
      - output of threat modelling
            - list of mitigations
            - risks
            - etc
      - various threat models methods 
            - STRIDE
            - DREAD
            - PASTA
            - LINDDUN
            - TRIKE
            - etc.
      - using Data Flow Diagrams (DFDs) in threat modelling
            - How DFDs support threat models
            - what do information flows represent
      - Trust boundaries and their importance in threat modelling
      - Common design flaws

